Gauteng Police Commissioner Elias Mawela is urging people not to take the law into their own hands. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng Police Commissioner Elias Mawela is urging people not to take the law into their own hands. He says immigration officers and law enforcement officials are the ones responsible for ensuring undocumented foreigners are dealt with accordingly. READ: ADF slams Operation Dudula This follows after a group called Operation Dudula took to the streets of Hillbrow, marching against crime. The group claims some undocumented foreigners are taking part in illegal criminal activities. Operation Dudula has vowed to return to Hillbrow this coming Saturday to continue its operation, this time with the relevant authorisation from law enforcement.